<body>
  <%= stylesheet_link_tag "custom_home", media: 'all', 'data-turbolinks-track' => true %>

    <nav class="navbar navbar-expand-lg navbar-light bg-light">
    <div class="container-fluid">
      <%= image_tag("stockMasterLogo.png", alt: "Stock Master Logo", style: "height:50px")%>
      <button class="navbar-toggler" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#navbarSupportedContent" aria-controls="navbarSupportedContent" aria-expanded="false" aria-label="Toggle navigation">
        <span class="navbar-toggler-icon"></span>
      </button>
      <div class="collapse navbar-collapse" id="navbarSupportedContent">
        <ul class="navbar-nav me-auto mb-2 mb-lg-0">
          <li class="nav-item">
            <a class="nav-link active" aria-current="page" style="font-size: 18px;padding-left: 20px">Hello <%= @username%>,</a>
          </li>
          <li class="nav-item"><%= link_to "Create order", orders_create_path, class: "nav-link", style: "font-size: 19px;" %></li>
          <li class="nav-item"><%= link_to "Track order", orders_track_path, class: "nav-link", style: "font-size: 19px;" %></li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        </ul>
        <ul class="navbar-nav ms-auto mb-2 mb-lg-0" style="margin-right: 20px;">
          <li class="nav-item">
            <%= link_to "Suppliers Info", suppliers_info_path, class: "nav-link", style: "font-size: 19px;" %>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <div style = "padding-left: 30px;" >
        <%= button_to "Log out", Current.session, method: :delete, class: "btn btn-outline-warning"%>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    </nav>
    <% if (notice)%>
      <div class="alert alert-success alert-dismissible fade show" role="alert" style="height:50px  ">
        <p style="color: green; margin-bottom: 0px;"><%= notice %></p>
      </div>
      <script>
        setTimeout(function() {
          document.querySelector('.alert').remove();
        }, 1600);
      </script>
    <%end %>
    <br>

  <div class="card" style="width: 95%;">
    <h1>Track Order</h1>
    <div class="card-container" id="cardContainer">
    <% @orders.each do |order|%>
      <div class="card mx-auto" style="width: 95%;margin-top: 20px;">
          <div class="card-body" >
              <h2>Order Number: <%= order.order_number %></h2>
              <p><strong>Stock Name:</strong> <%= Stock.find_by(id: order.stock_id).product_name%></p>
              <p><strong>Quantity:</strong> <%= order.quantity %> </p>
              <p><strong>Status:</strong> <%= order.status %> </p>
              <p><strong>Ordered on:</strong> <%= order.order_date %> </p>
              <p><strong>Amount:</strong> <%= order.total_amount %> </p>
              <p>
                 <%= form_tag cancel_order_path, method: :post do %>
                   <%= hidden_field_tag :order_id, order.id %>
                   <%= submit_tag 'Cancel Order', class: "btn btn-outline-danger"%>
                 <% end %>
Make sure you have the appropriate route set up for the cancel action in your config/routes.rb file:
ruby
Copy code
post '/orders/cancel_order', to: 'orders#cancel', as: :cancel_order
In your orders controller, set up the cancel action to handle the incoming order number and perform the cancellation logic:
ruby
Copy code
class OrdersController < ApplicationController
  # Existing actions and code

  def cancel
